"Greenwood International Private School Feedback on Alef and Arabits pathways" -  - This feedback is based on a recent follow-up visit with one of our schools. They reported several issues and feature requests regarding the platform:   (Ticket ID # 553949) -  -  - 1. Survey and feedback Display: Teachers reported frustration that the survey sent to them could not be skipped or snoozed when opening the platform during a lesson, which will oblige them to finish the survey in the lesson to be able to use the platform ( this happened with all schools). - 2. Activity Timing: They requested the ability to time activities, specifically setting a time limit in minutes for each question rather than having the time frame set in days (Exam questions in teacher activities). - 3. Download Feature: They would like an option to download the teacher-created activity tests after creation. - 4. Student Order in Analytics: When viewing the analytics page after creating tests using the "teacher activities" feature , the student names are not displayed in alphabetical order, making it difficult for them to transfer grades to their external files. - 5. Display Compatibility: Users reported that the bottom of certain pages is not fully visible unless they zoom out, suggesting that the standard page size may not be compatible with all devices and requires adjustment.

It has become evident that lessons directly aligned with the school curriculum are no longer available, as they previously were. This shift has had a considerable negative impact on the platform’s effectiveness in supporting classroom instruction. - In the past, the alignment between platform content and the curriculum allowed teachers to integrate Alef seamlessly into their lessons, which significantly enhanced students’ engagement, understanding, and academic progress. Moreover, the platform served as a valuable reference during review periods and exam preparation, offering both students and teachers a reliable tool for practice and reinforcement. - At present, however, the platform mainly provides reading texts accompanied by videos and questions that are unrelated to the actual lesson objectives. This misalignment does not serve the instructional goals, especially given the limited duration of a 45-minute class. Consequently, the platform’s usefulness to both teachers and students has been substantially reduced, and its role as an essential academic support has been undermined. - If this situation continues, the platform will no longer be integrated into daily lessons. Instead, its use will likely be restricted to one session per week, focusing solely on reading comprehension activities. This would significantly diminish the platform’s educational value and limit its contribution to the teaching and learning process. - In light of the above, I respectfully urge your esteemed management to reconsider this approach and restore direct alignment between the platform’s content and the school curriculum. Doing so will ensure that Alef continues to function as an effective educational tool, providing meaningful support to both students and teachers in achieving their academic goals. - Thank you for your kind attention to this matter. - Yours faithfully, - Alya Rashad Awad  - English teacher

Dear team,  -  - Please note that Icedmy is one of the private schools delivering their subjects entirely online. As an online school, they focus on providing a personalized learning experience for each student. - They are currently using both Alef AMS and Arabits Pathways. Yesterday, I had a detailed session with their team, during which they shared several suggestions and concerns that, if considered and implemented, could significantly enhance their learning experience and help them achieve their educational goals more effectively. -  - Below is a summary of the points for your kind review: - Suggestions: -  -  -  - Alef Core: - Enable the option to highlight more than one lesson simultaneously for unlocked students -  - When a lesson is unlocked, it should remain unlocked for all current and future students joining the class, instead of requiring manual unlocking for each new joiner - They would like to set different default locking behaviors for different grades, some with all lessons unlocked by default, and others with lessons locked, rather than applying the same rule across all grades - In both Alef Core and Arabits Pathways, it would be helpful if answer choices (especially in MCQs with audio) are numbered. This allows students to clearly refer to an answer by number, which is easier for teachers to track while teaching - Concerns: -  -  -  - Arabits Pathways: - In the Learning Section, when moving back and forth between cards, students cannot reattempt or change their answers unless the entire lesson is refreshed - They prefer having English translations for UI elements such as "ابدأ الدرس", "تأشيرة الخروج", and "أتعلم العربية" - In the videos, they recommend using Arabic captions instead of English, as students tend to focus on the English text and ignore the spoken Arabic. - They suggest using the correct Arabic word "صحيح" instead of "صح" when indicating a correct answer, for accuracy and consistency. - Please let me know if you need any further clarification. - Thank you all. -  - Requester: baraa.hakmi@alefeducation.com - School :Private - iCademy Middle East - 37594ps - Ticket:507691
